parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering unit can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to increased effort and potential loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the steering wheel requires increased effort to turn
the steering wheel locks up briefly
the steering feels stuck when turning
the steering effort increases during cold weather starts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a complete loss of the vehicle, and can also pose a risk to the safety of the occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or flames visible from the engine compartment
burning smell
engine overheating
engine stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive camshaft noise can be a sign of premature wear or failure, which can lead to engine damage, stalling, or failure, potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Loud knocking or grinding noise from the engine
engine stalling or misfiring
decreased engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cylinder pressure problems can cause intermittent stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Engine stalling or hesitation
loss of power
engine misfiring
difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's intermittent stalling can cause unexpected loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when starting in the morning
the vehicle stalls intermittently while driving
the engine dies or shuts off without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked windshield can obstruct the driver's view, compromising vehicle safety and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Cracks or chips on the windshield
obstructed view while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A coolant leak or clogged heater core can cause a hazardous situation, as the smell of antifreeze can be toxic and the buildup of film on the windshield can impair visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Unpleasant odor of antifreeze or gas inside the vehicle
film buildup on the windshield
inability to defrost the windshield
smell of coolant when using the heater.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The rear brakes do not engage
the rear brakes lock up when hard braking occurs
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake caliper can cause the rear brakes to malfunction, leading to reduced braking power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The rear brakes do not engage
the rear brakes lock up when hard braking occurs
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.
